Atiku Abubakar, presidential candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), has named Ifeanyi Okowa, governor of Delta, as his running mate in the 2023 general election. He announced his choice of running mate on Thursday at the PDP national headquarters in Abuja. He stated that he reached his decision after wide consultations with party stalwarts. Also Read: Nigerians’ll Vote Out APC In 2023 For Destroying Nation, Says Atiku He revealed that it was a difficult decision for him for to make considering the quality of those that were recommended. Announcing the decision on his Twitter handle, Atiku wrote: I am delighted to announce Governor @IAOkowa as my Vice Presidential candidate. I look forward to travelling our great country together, engaging with all Nigerians and building a shared future of peace, unity, and prosperity for all. As One We Can Get It Done. #OneNigeria. -AA pic.twitter.com/JyKxTIhiUh — Atiku Abubakar (@atiku) June 16, 2022  